g.text: - Users can view a feed of their friend's posts (chronological order)
- Users can page through their feed
- Prioritize availability over consistency, up to 2 minutes for eventual consistency
use graphdb like Neo4j, node is User, edge is Friendship
query FeedEntry table for specific userId, sort by createdAt, return postId
SELECT postId FROM FeedEntry WHERE userId="xyz" ORDER BY createdAt
when post is created, POST_CREATED event is emitted. Feed service listens, fetches users
following the poster and creates a FeedEntry for each user with that postId
- Generate feed at write time (when new post is created) or read time (when feed is fetched)?
- to make feed fetching fast, we pre-generate feed at write time, so when a user requests
their feed, we already have the list of posts to show them waiting
- What if a single user has millions of followers?
- don't fanout-on-write posts from users with lots of followers, flag them and aggregate
